      "lesson title": "AI in Manufacturing Supply Chains",
      "order": 1,
      "Description": "This lesson introduces how artificial intelligence is being applied across manufacturing supply chains, with a focus on the practical risks that come with adopting these technologies. You will explore how AI is used in demand forecasting, procurement decisions, and logistics automation, and why each of these areas carries its own set of challenges. We will look at real-world examples to help you understand where things can go wrong, from inaccurate predictions to over-reliance on automated systems. By the end of this lesson, you will have a clearer picture of how to approach AI adoption in supply chain contexts with greater awareness and confidence.",
