          "number": 3,
          "slidetitle": "Forecasting Risks and Inaccuracies",
          "subtitle": "Where predictions fall short in practice",
          "slidecontent": "• AI forecasts rely on historical data, so sudden market shifts or disruptions can catch models off guard\n• Garbage in, garbage out\n• Seasonal spikes, new product launches, and geopolitical events are notoriously difficult for algorithms to predict accurately\n• Small errors in demand forecasting can ripple outward, causing overstock or critical shortages across the supply chain\n• Real-world data is often incomplete, inconsistent, or delayed, undermining forecast reliability from the start\n• Human oversight remains essential to catch and correct predictions before they drive costly decisions"
