          "number": 4,
          "slidetitle": "Procurement Risks and AI Bias",
          "subtitle": "Hidden biases in automated sourcing decisions",
          "slidecontent": "• AI sourcing tools trained on historical data can inherit past supplier preferences, even when those preferences were based on outdated or unfair criteria\n• Bias often invisible to procurement teams reviewing only the final recommendation\n• Smaller or newer suppliers may be systematically ranked lower, limiting competition and innovation\n• Geographic and cultural gaps in training data skew results toward familiar markets\n• Auditing AI decisions regularly helps surface patterns that no single purchase order would reveal"
