          "slidecontent": "• AI sourcing tools trained on historical data can inherit past supplier preferences, excluding newer or more diverse vendors\n• Biased outputs often go unnoticed because the system appears objective\n• Cost and speed metrics may be over-weighted, pushing out smaller, local, or sustainable suppliers\n• Lack of transparency in how decisions are ranked makes auditing difficult\n• Procurement teams need to regularly review and challenge automated recommendations"
